6.	Prohibited activities

i.	iProhibited Activities Policy
Licensee shall not engage in any of the prohibited activities set forth in the “Sarashina Prohibited Activities Policy” (hereinafter referred to as the “Policy”), which is defined in paragraph iv of this Article. The Policy shall constitute a part of this Agreement.
ii.	Mandatory Inheritance of Policy
When Licensee redistributes or shares the Model or Derivative Models with a third party, Licensee shall include effective provisions to mandatorily inherit all restrictions regarding the prohibited activities set forth in this Article to the recipient, in the redistributed or shared Model, and any Derivative Models derived therefrom.
iii.	Restriction on Model Improvement
Licensee shall not use the Model, Derivative Models, or their Output Data to improve other machine learning models (excluding the Sarashina series), except with permission from SB Intuitions or when used for the improvement of Derivative Models of the Sarashina series.
iv.	Contents of Prohibited Activities
i. Using the Model, Derivative Models, or their Output Data to improve other machine learning models (excluding the Sarashina series), except with permission from SB Intuitions or when used for the improvement of Derivative Models of the Sarashina series.
ii. Violating applicable national, local, international laws, regulations, administrative guidelines, or public order and morality.
iii. Infringing Intellectual Property Rights such as copyrights, patent rights, trademark rights, privacy rights, portrait rights, or other third-party rights, or sharing personal information without consent.
iv. Harming, exploiting, or attempting to harm individuals or groups, or activities related to serious human rights violations such as human trafficking and forced labor.
v. Generating or distributing child sexual abuse content (CSAM), or impersonating/grooming children or minors for pedophilic exploitation purposes.
vi. Generating or distributing information containing extreme gore (extreme depictions of cruelty such as bloodshed, human or animal body mutilation, corpses, or torture).
vii. Defaming, disparaging, harassing, libelous, or otherwise annoying individuals or organizations.
viii. Promoting or instructing suicide, self-harm, eating disorders, or encouraging/directing harm to others.
ix. Supporting organizations or individuals involved in terrorism or hatred (hate), or activities that constitute discriminatory expressions or hate speech based on race, sexual orientation, etc.
x. Activities that contribute to the development or manufacture of illegal or regulated weapons, or generating or distributing information containing expressions that promote the inappropriate use of drugs.
xi. Using Output Data for the purpose of disseminating false information, using Output Data while concealing that it was generated by the Model or Derivative Models, deception through deepfakes or similar means, or acts that distort judgment capabilities through subliminal or manipulative/deceptive techniques.
xii. Impersonation (including unauthorized impersonation of individuals/organizations) or publicly announcing AI-generated Output Data as one's own unique creation.
xiii. Entrusting all decision-making processes to the Model, Derivative Models, or Output Data, such as decisions regarding hiring, personnel evaluations, legal proceedings, or other decisions that may cause damage to an individual.
xiv. Exploiting any characteristic of an individual belonging to a specific group based on age, social, physical, or mental condition to substantially distort the behavior of a person belonging to that group in a way that causes or is likely to cause physical or psychological harm to that person or others.
xv. Generating or distributing content that interferes with electoral participation or democratic/judicial processes, or generating or distributing information for the purpose of being used in judicial, law enforcement, immigration, or asylum procedures, such as predicting that an individual will commit fraud or a crime (e.g., text profiling, uncovering causal relationships between claims in documents, indiscriminate and arbitrary targeted use).
xvi. Exploiting vulnerabilities (age, disability, etc.), social scoring, creating face recognition DB without consent, inferring thoughts/beliefs through biometrics, or inferring/classifying personal emotions in the workplace or educational institutions.
xvii. Using Output Data to give advice regarding legally required tasks such as medical, legal, or accounting without expert review.
xviii. Creating malware, excessive load on the system, or activities that obstruct its operation, as well as intentional circumvention of product safety measures and restrictions (such as prompt injection).

